The deadline to apply for P-EBT food benefits has been extended to Friday, August 21 2020. Friday is the LAST day to apply!
Did your child receive free or reduced-price school meals through the National School Lunch Program during the 2019-2020 school
year? If so, your family may be eligible for this one-time food benefit. Visit hhs.texas.gov/pebt to learn more about P-EBT.
For questions regarding eligibility or if you need help applying, contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220. The public charge rule does not apply to P-EBT benefits.

We'd like to wish our campus leader, Ms. Jones, a very happy National School Principal's Day!! We are honored and thankful to call you our school principal.

A native El Pasoan, Ms. Jones has worked in education as a math teacher, business teacher, student activities manager, assistant principal, principal, and educational consultant at several campuses throughout her career‚Äìat the middle school, high school, and college levels.

Points of pride include being the founding principal of Transmountain Early College High School and awarded Region 19 Principal of the Year!!

To learn more about Ms. Jones and our faculty and staff visit: www.epleadershipacademy.org/staff/

post_text:
Families,

We hope this message finds you and your family safe and well.

First, a huge thank you and shout out to all of our teachers, staff, scholars, and families who helped us seamlessly transition into our distance-learning program. We look forward to finishing the year strong!

As you know we are continuing to monitor the COVID-19 outbreak and its impact on our school. As we continue to follow orders from government officials, we will be extending the campus closure until Monday, May 4, 2020. We understand that as the date approaches and new developments arise, we may not be able to return to campus for the remainder of the school year. We will continue to provide timely updates to our families.

Regardless of the circumstances, we have full confidence in our teachers, families, and scholars to remain on course and finish the academic year strong!

Mr. Casillas is available through the Remind app or email for any questions jcasillas@epleadershipacademy.org

Please continue to monitor our communication channels for any updates or changes to our plans.

EPLA Leadership Team

post_text:
Families!

The El Paso Leadership Academy announced today it will continue its policy to operate the Community Eligibility Program (CEP) under the National School Lunch Program and School Breakfast Program for the 2019-2020 school year.

Schools qualifying to operate CEP serve breakfast and lunch to all children at no charge and eliminate the collection of meal applications for free, reduced-price, and paid student meals. This new approach reduces burdens for both families and school administrators and helps ensure that students receive nutritious meals.

For additional information please contact Emily Levario at elevario@epleadershipacademy.org

To access the breakfast and lunch menu please visit: http://www.epleadershipacademy.org/menus/

Why Do Our Parents Choose EPLA for Their Children?

National School Choice Week is an annual showcase designed to show parents the various K-12 educational choices available for their children, including conventional public schools, public charter schools, public magnet schools, homeschooling, private schools, and online academies. For 2019, NSCW will be held from January 20 through January 26.

Read more;
